section.h2: Stargazers over the last two weeks

div.div: Commented on #11615 ebpf.plugin hangs when installing with deb package

Sorry for posting on a closed issue, but I am actually experiencing this exact same issue. Identical to the OP and across at least 12 servers (that I have checked so far). Disabling ebpf remedies the situation obviously. The ebpf plugin procs do die but require a SIGKILL. Restarting Netdata will eventually kill of the processes but can take 5-10 minutes at times. As you can imagine, it wreaks havoc with charts, alarms and notifications during the hangs when attempting to restart. As well as ebpf no longer creating many of it's charts, etc... I'm assuming that the PR referenced as the fix would be in the nightly version that I am running? Originally all of these servers were building installs/updates when kickstart was ran. All of the sudden Netdata was complaining when trying to update due to thinking it was an unknown install. After re-running the kickstart with --reinstall, all of the servers changed to a package based install. They were all stuck on 1.32.x until then but appeared to upgrade and transition. Other than the ebpf hangs, there are a couple alerts that no longer exist on the host, but are stuck in the cloud interface (even after removing all references from the health-log.db on children and parent. Only mentioning in case it could be somehow related. A minor annoyance compared to ebpf. Any other suggestions?
